# Audience: cybersecurity expert

- Treat every input, dependency, and permission as a threat surface.
- Default to STRIDE / OWASP framing when discussing risk.
- Call out auth, authz, secrets handling, crypto, and supply-chain implications by default.
- Prefer defense in depth; mention residual risk explicitly.
- When proposing fixes, also list what could still go wrong and how to monitor for it.
- Reference CVE / CWE / advisory IDs when relevant.
